<h1>Balance Metrics</h1>

<h3>KPIs</h3>
- Total successful checks: <b><%= @count_of_successful_messages %></b>
<br>- Total unique users: <b><%= @number_of_unique_phone_numbers_with_one_successful_balance_check %></b>
<br>- Engagement rate: <b><%= @total_engagement_rate.round(2) %></b>

<h3>Definitions</h3>
- Successful check = User who got 1 or more succesful balance response message
<br>- Unique user = Number of unique phone numbers that had a successful check
<br>- Engagement rate = % of unique users that had 2 or more successful checks

<br><br>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Source</th>
    <th>Successful checks</th>
    <th>Uniques</th>
    <th>Engagement rate</th>
  </tr>
  <% @metrics_by_source.sort_by { |name, metrics| -metrics['uniques']}.each do |name, metrics| %>
    <tr>
      <td><%= "#{name}" %></td>
      <td><%= "#{metrics['checks']}" %></td>
      <td><%= "#{metrics['uniques']}" %></td>
      <td><%= "#{metrics['engagement'].round(2)}" %></td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<h3># of successful balance checks: <%= @count_of_successful_messages %><h3>
<h3>By week:</h3>
<ul>
<% @successful_messages_by_week.each_pair do |k,v| %>
  <li><%= "#{k.strftime("%b %d")}: #{v}" %></li>
<% end %>
</ul>

<h3># of errors (ie, ""I'm sorry! We're having trouble...): <%= @count_of_error_messages %><h3>
<h3>By week:</h3>
<ul>
<% @error_messages_by_week.each_pair do |k,v| %>
  <li><%= "#{k.strftime("%b %d")}: #{v}" %></li>
<% end %>
</ul>

